<item>
            <title>[PDFBOX-4693] PDF documents with rotated form field(90&#176; degrees in my case) that apply form flattening appear squ</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-4693</link>
                <project id="12310760" key="PDFBOX">PDFBox</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Overview:  Created a PDF form through Adobe PDF Creation tool. Rotate field(90&#176;) to fit design of PDF. Have PDFBox load the PDF form get Acroform set the form fields and have acroform apply flattening.. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Expectation: When flattening is applied. Rotated(90&#176;) fields value would print out rotated and normal size.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Issue: When flattening is applied. Rotated(90&#176;) fields values seemed squished or flattened.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also one thing that might not have been clear .. This issue didn&apos;t seem to exist in version 2.0.16 (or prior that I know of)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
