                            <comment id="16978660" author="tilman" created="Wed, 20 Nov 2019 18:32:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-4615&quot; title=&quot;AppearanceGeneratorHelper.setAppearanceValue doesn&amp;#39;t set the bounding box on the appearance stream correctly&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-4615&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-4615&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; did this &#128557;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I must have missed that it is possible to have single rotated fields. I assume this is done in &lt;tt&gt;AP/N/Matrix&lt;/tt&gt;. (makes me wonder whether it is possible to have 28&#176; rotated fields?)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16980295" author="jira-bot" created="Fri, 22 Nov 2019 16:27:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1870170 from Tilman Hausherr in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1870170&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1870170&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-4693&quot; title=&quot;PDF documents with rotated form field(90&#176; degrees in my case) that apply form flattening appear squ&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-4693&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-4693&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: consider rotation of the appearance stream matrix instead of the page rotation&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16980296" author="jira-bot" created="Fri, 22 Nov 2019 16:27:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1870171 from Tilman Hausherr in branch &apos;pdfbox/branches/issue4569&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
