&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-4693&quot; title=&quot;PDF documents with rotated form field(90&#176; degrees in my case) that apply form flattening appear squ&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-4693&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-4693&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: consider rotation of the appearance stream matrix instead of the page rotation&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16980299" author="jira-bot" created="Fri, 22 Nov 2019 16:27:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1870173 from Tilman Hausherr in branch &apos;pdfbox/branches/2.0&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1870173&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1870173&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-4693&quot; title=&quot;PDF documents with rotated form field(90&#176; degrees in my case) that apply form flattening appear squ&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-4693&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-4693&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: consider rotation of the appearance stream matrix instead of the page rotation&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16980310" author="tilman" created="Fri, 22 Nov 2019 16:41:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Turns out that it is enough to just check the matrix angle instead of the page rotation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But while testing I discovered a different problem, which is why I&apos;m reopening &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-4666&quot; title=&quot;StackOverflowError with PDFTextStripper.getText()&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-4666&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-4666&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/sad.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; This means that rendering the flattened files might not work properly, until I&apos;ve reverted the changes there. But the PDF files should be OK.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please test your code with a snapshot build and confirm it works, now on &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://repository.apache.org/content/groups/snapshots/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfbox-app/2.0.18-SNAPSHOT/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://repository.apache.org/content/groups/snapshots/org/apache/pdfbox/pdfbox-app/2.0.18-SNAPSHOT/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
(at the bottom, number 115 or higher)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I used only file 3 to test, and I also included a test with it in our build tests.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16980317" author="taxdawg" created="Fri, 22 Nov 2019 16:51:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tilman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tilman&quot;&gt;tilman&lt;/a&gt; Thanks so much for looking into this .. I will test later today on a couple of documents. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16980620" author="taxdawg" created="Sat, 23 Nov 2019 02:02:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tilman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tilman&quot;&gt;tilman&lt;/a&gt; Sorry I didn&apos;t get back to you till now.. I checked it out on my end and it seems that the pdf that was causing me some issue is working as expected.. once again thanks a lot for your work. Before your work I was stuck&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
